headline: CrowdStrike Holdings (NasdaqGS:CRWD) Partners With Arrow Electronics To Expand Falcon Platform In North America
summary: CrowdStrike Holdings (NasdaqGS:CRWD) experienced a price movement of 4.9% over the last quarter. During this period, the company's strategic initiatives, such as the newly announced distribution agreement with Arrow Electronics, aimed to bolster its channel partnerships and expand the availability of its Falcon cybersecurity platform. headline: CrowdStrike Shares Sink on Outlook. Should Investors Buy the Stock on the Dip?
summary: CrowdStrike (NASDAQ: CRWD) shares tumbled after the company issued weak profitability guidance for fiscal year 2026 and saw spending from existing customers continue to decelerate.  The company's stock saw a big pullback last summer after a well-publicized outage, but the stock had nicely recovered until this recent sell-off.  Let's take a closer look at CrowdStrike's most recent results and guidance to see whether this dip is a good opportunity to buy the stock.
